message.content:
Customer Service Representative

Key Responsibilities

1. Confer with customers by telephone or in person to provide information about products or services. 2. Take or enter orders, cancel accounts, or obtain details of complaints.

Key Skills

1. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills. 2. Ability to remain calm and composed in high-pressure situations. 3. Strong problem-solving and conflict resolution skills. 4. Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and prioritize tasks effectively.

Key Qualifications

1. High school diploma or equivalent required. 2. Previous customer service experience preferred. 3. Ability to work a flexible schedule, including evenings and weekends.

Key Tools and Technologies

1. Telephone and computer systems for communication and data entry. 2. CRM software for tracking customer interactions and orders. 3. Product knowledge and training on company services and policies.
